body:
After #462, we have Docker support in the repo.
This PR will modify the corresponding updates in Livedoc.

@marevol, please help to check if I make any mistake.

@chanlee514 please review.

@shimamoto you may want to include this in your PMC doc update.

This addresses warnings when tarball is created using non-GNU tar (e.g. macOS). Here's an [example](https://superuser.com/questions/318809/linux-os-x-tar-incompatibility-tarballs-created-on-os-x-give-errors-when-unt).

Fixes [PIO-120](https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIO-120)

This changeset ensures that the process exits gracefully after ES connection error.

Apologies for the indentation shift. This changeset simply wraps the body of the main function with:

```scala
try {
  // much existing code
} finally {
  CleanupFunctions.run()
}
```
